{
  "answer": "**The term \"lehd\" (or variants like \"lahd\" or \"lḥd\"), referring to the niche or alcove within a grave in Urdu poetic and Islamic burial terminology, does not appear in the English translations or transliterations of *Diwan-e-Ghalib* available in this corpus.**\n\nGhalib frequently evokes the grave (*gor*) as a metaphor for death, longing, paradise, or the lover's torment—common in Urdu ghazal tradition—but uses *gor* rather than *lehd*. Examples include:\n\n- In ghazal 17: Contemplating the beloved's beauty opens \"a door to paradise\" *within my very grave*.[^1]\n- In ghazal 30: The speaker's desire for bodily ease leads him *to the grave*, yet even there, chaos denies peace.[^2]\n- In ghazal 78: *My heart bleeds in the grave*; the beloved's nails now need henna, not the lover's blood.[^3]\n- In ghazal 98: *The madman's grave* becomes a playground for children after death.[^4]\n- In ghazal 233: The speaker is a \"burnt-out lamp upon a *pauper's grave*\" (*gor-e-ghareebaan* in the original).[^5]\n\nIf \"lehd\" appears in a specific edition or lesser-known verse not digitized here (the corpus covers 239 ghazals), it is absent from searchable English bodies and sampled transliterations. For broader Urdu poetry, terms like *gor* or *qabr* dominate Ghalib's imagery of mortality and love.[^6]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-be2c8d](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/17-bazm-e-shahanshah-mein-ashaar-ka-daftar-khula/translation/#p-be2c8d).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-17a207](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/30-dekh-kar-dar-parda-garm-daaman-afshaani-mujhe/translation/#p-17a207).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-9e89fe](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/78-husn-ghamze-ki-kashakash-se-chhoota-mere-baad/translation/#p-9e89fe).\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-24b5ab](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/98-junoon-tohmat-kash-e-taskeen-na-ho-gar-shadmani-ki/translation/#p-24b5ab).\n[^5]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [p-6dbbbe](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/233-sitaish-gar-hai-zahid-is-qadar-jis-bagh-e-rizwan-k/translation/#p-6dbbbe).\n[^6]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 17 [transliteration](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/17-bazm-e-shahanshah-mein-ashaar-ka-daftar-khula/transliteration/) (\"gor\"); ch. 30 [transliteration](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/30-dekh-kar-dar-parda-garm-daaman-afshaani-mujhe/transliteration/) (\"gor\").",
